                            <div class="module insetHFullWidth">
                                <div class="shareTools shareToolsThemeClassic shareToolsThemeClassicHorizontal shareToolsThemeClassicDark interactive970BlackStandardShareTools" data-shares="facebook,twitter,google,email,showall|Share" data-title="On the Front Line" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2013/02/09/nyregion/neediest-cases-on-the-front-line.html"
                                    data-description="Social workers discuss their involvement with the Neediest Cases Fund and their profession."></div>
                                <meta name="emailThisHash" content="BcRiiNue81n2pteR6tzHRw">
                                <div class="storyHeader">
                                    <h6 class="dateline">
                                        <span>Published: </span>February 9, 2013 </h6>
                                    <h6 class="kicker">The Neediest Cases</h6>
                                    <h1>On the Front Line</h1>
                                </div>
                                <p class="summary feedback">
                                    Social workers discuss their involvement with the Neediest Cases Fund and their profession.
                                    <span class="noWrap refer">
                    
                                                
                        
                                                    <a class="refer" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/10/nyregion/for-times-neediest-cases-fund-a-campaign-touched-by-a-storm.html">Related Article &#xBB;</a>
                                                
                    </span>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div id="interactiveFreeFormMain">
                                <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://static01.nyt.com/packages/css/multimedia/bundles/projects/2013/Neediest.css">
                                <div id="nytmm_container" data-style="display:none;">
                                    <div id="nytmm_loader">
                                        <div id="nytmm_storyBook1" class="nytmm_storyBook">
                                            <div class="nytmm_storyBook_nav">
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBook_nav_title">
                                                    <h2 class="nytmm_storyBook_nav_hed"></h2>
                                                    <h3 class="nytmm_storyBook_nav_subHed"></h3>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="nytmm_storyBook_screen nytmm_storyBook_screenFirst nytmm_storyBook_template_leadArtSecondaryArt nytmm_storyBook_template_leadLeft">
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBookNav_chapter_nav">
                                                    <h5 class="nytmm_storyBookNav_chapter_kicker"></h5>
                                                    <h4 class="nytmm_storyBookNav_chapter_hed"></h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBook_mediaContainer">
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/01/25/nyregion/25social-weiss/25social-weiss-custom1.jpg">
                                                        <div class="img-credit">Chester Higgins Jr./The New York Times</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLabel"><span>Nicki Weiss</span></p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLocation">Westchester Jewish Community Services</p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_slideQuote">&quot;Social workers are asked to do more with less. It&#x2019;s sort of like a mirror experience to our clients, who are also in their private lives being asked to do more with less. I think social
                                                            workers often feel that they are on the journey with them, that you&#x2019;re walking the walk with them. And that in itself has a lot of merit for the client. &#x2018;There, but for the grace
                                                            of God, go I,&#x2019; so I want to be the person that I would want someone to be in my life if I needed that same help.&#x201D;</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="nytmm_storyBook_screen nytmm_storyBook_template_leadArtSecondaryArt nytmm_storyBook_template_leadLeft">
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBook_mediaContainer">
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/02/09/nyregion/social-fia/social-fia-custom1.jpg">
                                                        <div class="img-credit">Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLabel"><span>Fia Sarmi</span></p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLocation">Catholic Charities Brooklyn &amp; Queens</p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_slideQuote">&quot;I wasn&apos;t born in a fortunate family. I actually came from a very third world country, from the poorest country in Southeast Asia. Therefore I know I can relate to each one of my clients
                                                            and where they are coming from. Whether they have a fridge, no fridge. Whether they have a roof over their head, or no roof over their heads. I know how it feels, I understand. And that&apos;s
                                                            what inspires me to fight for them. No one wants to say, &apos;Oh, I want to be homeless. Oh, I don&#x2019;t want to pay my bills.&apos;&quot;</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="nytmm_storyBook_screen nytmm_storyBook_template_leadArtSecondaryArt nytmm_storyBook_template_leadLeft">
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBook_mediaContainer">
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/01/28/nyregion/neediest-fernandez/neediest-fernandez-custom1.jpg">
                                                        <div class="img-credit">Tony Cenicola/The New York Times</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLabel"><span>Jorge Fernandez</span></p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLocation">Brooklyn Community Services</p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_slideQuote">&quot;We are the front lines of so many things out there. We&apos;re almost first responders in a way. We handle all sorts of situations, whether it&apos;s problems of finances, or problems of mental
                                                            illness or whatever emotional or concrete issue really anyone would be dealing with. It&apos;s a social worker that&apos;s confronting that. We&apos;re one of the strongest professions out there
                                                            I think, especially in New York City.&quot;</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="nytmm_storyBook_screen nytmm_storyBook_template_leadArtSecondaryArt nytmm_storyBook_template_leadLeft">
                                                <div class="nytmm_storyBook_mediaContainer">
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/01/25/nyregion/25social-steph/25social-steph-custom1.jpg">
                                                        <div class="img-credit">Chester Higgins Jr./The New York Times</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="nytmm_storyBook_media">
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLabel"><span>Stephanie Harrill</span></p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_bioLocation">Catholic Charities, The Archdiocese of New York</p>
                                                        <p class="nytmm_slideQuote">&quot;With the downturn of the economy, there are people turning to social services that didn&#x2019;t before. There is an increase in the clients who didn&#x2019;t want to have to use services but
                                                            they&#x2019;ve gotten to that point and then we have to go into crisis mode. Sometimes people hear the title social worker and expect that immediate step because we should know how to do everything.
                                                            It&#x2019;s awesome because we have the ability to do so many different things and at the same time challenging because the expectation is there. But sometimes we need a little more backing or
                                                            a little more time.&quot;</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
